Now that the structures are in place we need to swap out the {THING:CircuitboardAirlockControl}  for the {THING:CircuitboardAdvAirlockControl} 

There are only a few differences when programing the  {THING:CircuitboardAdvAirlockControl}. Firstly you need to select and internal and external {THING:StructureActiveVent} unlike doors you will need to look at the switch on the {THING:StructureActiveVent} to see if it’s interactable or not this is how you can decipher which {THING:StructureActiveVent} corresponds to the ones on the menu.

The last thing you need to do is select the pressure you want for both the internal and external pressure found near the top of the panel.
